[001] Installation
________________________________________________________________________________

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                              |
|  $ kiss b mlb                                                                |
|                                                                              |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+


[002] Setup
________________________________________________________________________________

Backup your current MBR.

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                              |
|  $ dd if=/dev/sdXY of=/boot/mbr.bak bs=512 count=1                           |
|                                                                              |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

--[003] MBR --------------------------------------------------------------------

  +----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  |                                                                            |
  |  $ mlbinstall /dev/sdX /boot/vmlinuz root=/dev/sdXY ro loglevel=3 quiet    |
  |                                                                            |
  +----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

--[004] VBR --------------------------------------------------------------------

  Passing -vbr to mlbinstall will make mlbinstall ignore the space for the
  partition table, giving you 144 bytes for the command line. You can safely
  use it if you're installing to a Volume Boot Record (partition), e.g. for
  using with another bootloader in multi-OS setups.

